SIMPLE: wiper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wiper
<hw>Wip"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or
that which, wipes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something used for wiping, as a towel or
rag.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A piece generally projecting from
a rotating or swinging piece, as an axle or rock shaft, for the purpose
of raising stampers, lifting rods, or the like, and leaving them to fall
by their own weight; a kind of cam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Firearms)</fld> <def>A rod, or an attachment for a
rod, for holding a rag with which to wipe out the bore of the
barrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wirble</ent>⟦br⟧
